<HEADLINE>
<P>
TODAY'S QUOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"It was the way you always dreamed it would be, and never is, except during the 
Olympics and on holidays. There was absolutely no traffic." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Rick Ruiz, a deputy to City Councilwoman Ruth Galanter, commenting on a 
lack of freeway congestion Monday credited to the "semi-holiday" of the third 
of July, when thousands of workers -- and commuters -- took the day off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
