<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: CM COMMUNICATIONS PLANS TO GO PUBLIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CM Communications announced that it would go public with a sale of 1 million 
common shares and hope to raise as much as $3.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
The Panorama City distributor of cellular telephone equipment said in a filing 
with the federal Securities and Exchange Commission that it would use "a 
substantial portion" of the proceeds from the offering to finance a new 
subsidiary that will import cellular communications equipment. 
</P>
<P>
CM said that after the offering, officers and directors of the firm would own 
about 27% of the shares. CM reported a loss of $500,000 on sales of $11.3 
million for the nine months ended September 30, 1988, the last period for which 
it produced audited financial information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
