<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carlos Monzon, former middleweight champion, was convicted of homicide in the 
February 1988 death of his longtime companion, Alicia Muniz. 
</P>
<P>
Monzon, 47, was sentenced to 11 years in prison and ordered to pay court costs 
and $25,000 to Muniz's family. He won the middleweight title on May 7, 1970, 
from Italy's Nino Benvenuti, and defended it 14 times before retiring in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
An appeal is possible to the Supreme Court of Buenos Aires Province. Monzon, 
present at the reading of the sentence, did not say whether he intended to do 
so. 
</P>
