<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOURTH OF JULY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today is Independence Day, a celebration of the signing of the Declaration of 
Independence on July 4, 1776. The following will be closed in observance of the 
holiday: 
</P>
<P>
All city, county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
Schools, including colleges and universities. 
</P>
<P>
County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
All post offices. Mail deposited in mailboxes will be picked up according to 
the posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
TRASH: There will be no trash pickup today, and refuse collection throughout 
the county will be a day late the rest of the week. 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY TRANSIT DISTRICT: Buses will run on holiday schedules today. 
There will be no dial-a-ride or car-pool services available today. 
</P>
<P>
PARKS: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
regular hours today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
