<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIREWORKS MAY HAVE SPARKED 3 BLAZES ON ROOFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three small roof fires Monday at adjacent homes in Seal Beach were probably 
related to fireworks, but the cause remains under investigation, fire officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The first fire was reported at 5:37 p.m. at 4424 Elder Ave., a county fire 
spokesman said. Moderate damage was reported to the roof and attic, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Two adjacent roofs suffered similar damage in the three-alarm incident, 
officials said, after they were apparently ignited by sparks from the first 
house. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
